{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/organisations/health-equity-in-health-protection-initiative/about","content_id":"68a0b211-4cac-44b7-bc33-16a9bd678f26","description":"The Health Equity in Health Protection Initiative (HEHPI) provides a central, external-facing platform that brings together UKHSA’s key health equity resources in one place. It helps ensure that data, research, and community insights are easier to find, use, and share.","details":{"attachments":[],"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><h2 id=\"what-we-do\">What we do</h2>\n\n<p>The Health Equity in Health Protection Initiative supports UKHSA’s cross-cutting goal to deliver more equitable health outcomes. The initiative does this by helping UKHSA to build a strong foundation of data and evidence relevant to health equity in health protection. This includes understanding:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the differential impact of health protection hazards on <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.england.nhs.uk/about/equality/equality-hub/national-healthcare-inequalities-improvement-programme/core20plus5/\">CORE20PLUS</a> and inclusion health groups</li>\n  <li>what interventions are most effective in reducing health inequalities in health protection</li>\n  <li>how communities experience and engage with health services</li>\n</ul>\n\n</div>","change_history":[{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2025-09-11T08:44:31Z"}],"corporate_information_groups":[],"headers":[{"id":"what-we-do","level":2,"text":"What we do"}],"organisation":"ddbcf126-26cf-4f12-bcae-7c41fffc8ae8","tags":{"browse_pages":[]}},"document_type":"about","first_published_at":"2025-09-11T09:44:31+01:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/health-equity-in-health-protection-initiative/about","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/health-equity-in-health-protection-initiative/about","base_path":"/government/organisations/health-equity-in-health-protection